<paragraph blockId="147.[151,1436,404,503]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">
A monotypic genus (for identification see 
<bibRefCitation author="Garrison, R. W. &amp; von Ellenrieder, N. &amp; Louton, J. A." box="[620,846,441,468]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" refId="ref191047" refString="Garrison, R. W., von Ellenrieder, N. &amp; Louton, J. A. (2006) The Dragonfly Genera (Odonata: Anisoptera of the New World. An Illustrated and Annotated Key. Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore, 368 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Garrison 
<emphasis box="[724,780,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
). Adults are mostly brown (
<figureCitation box="[1153,1235,440,467]" captionStart="FIGURE 85" captionStartId="147.[151,250,1959,1984]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,993,1940]" captionTargetId="figure@147.[227,1361,993,1940]" captionTargetPageId="147" captionText="FIGURE 85. Argyrothemis argentea ♂, ECUADOR, Sucumbíos Province, Shushufindi, trails, small steams 3 km W of Shushufindi, 2+ km N off Hwy. 26 at km marker 17, 14 x 2009, photo J. T. Johnson." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335791/files/figure.png" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
). Habitat is small, shaded forest streams.
</paragraph>
